text.section:
"Environmental services" means the benefits generated for society by the existence and dynamic development of forests, including:
Producing oxygen and removing carbon dioxide from the atmosphere;
Regulating the surface and underground flow of water;
Providing effective filtration systems for higher water quality;
Supporting a myriad of native flora and fauna; and
Providing goods and services ranging from forest products to aesthetics.

"Forestry" or "silviculture" means the science, art, and practice of creating, managing, using, and conserving forests and associated resources for human benefit and in a sustainable manner to meet desired goals, including goals for:
Clean air and water;
Biodiversity;
Wildlife habitat;
Fiber production; and
Recreation.

section.section:
"Forestry practices" includes:
Planting;
Prescribed burning;
Thinning;
Pruning;
Harvesting;
Fertilizing; and
Pesticide and herbicide application.

text.section:
"Sustainable forestry" or "sustainable forestry management" means an internationally accepted and applied stewardship concept for the use of forests and forest lands in a manner and at a rate that maintains a forest's:
Biodiversity;
Productivity;
Regeneration capacity;
Nutrient reduction benefits;
Vitality; and
Ecological, economic, and social purposes at local and national levels that do not cause damage to other ecosystems.
